KEEPING THE DREAMS ALIVE - MY COVID 19 JOURNEYWhy do @grabfoodsg ? And how have your live change?The earnings may not be much, but it serves as my passive income. Before the start of every week, I will calculate the possible or expected total expenditure amount. I will then work hard to meet the targeted amount. For example, if I know that Iâ€™m going to have a meeting at @starbuckssg , and I will probably be spending, $30. I will do my delivery rides between classes or after classes to obtain the amount.However hard the circumstances are, I will never give up on my responsibilities and my dreams. I will keep my dreams alive.Arenâ€™t you ashamed? There is a possibility that you will meet your clients or colleagues?Certainly, the possibility of meeting any of them is there. But personally, there is nothing to be ashamed of.Have you ever seen, the physically challenged individuals who are working? Or even the elderlies?I am more ashamed if I donâ€™t do anything to better myself or my situation given that I am able bodied and capable.Iâ€™ve never been ashamed doing any kind of jobs as long as I know that whatever im doing is permissible in the eye of the nationâ€™s law and from the perspective of my religion. Like many of us, I come from a family which encountered many hardships yet we continue to strive for excellence.When I was younger, my brother and I, we used to buy cartons of can drinks from @shengsiongsupermarket_official and put them in Styrofoam boxes filled with ice made from home. We then tie the boxes on to the additional passenger seats on our bicycles. We will cycle to hard to reach areas at East Coast Park, basketball courts and street soccer courts to sell them. Besides that, we also gave tuitions and worked as hotel dishwasher at Grand Hyatt. We paid for our A-level examination fees and we never ask from our parents for our school pocket money.To all of you out there if youâ€™re contemplating, thereâ€™s nothing to be ashamed of.#resilienteconomy #startuplife #socialtechnopreneur #student #grabfoodsg #shengsiongsupermarket
